{"article_id":"b3SDhkCc9yUrDAOJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As usual , there are some worrisome data points in a generally Trump-positive poll ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"but start with the good news for the president :","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"A new national survey from CNN shows","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"public support for his handling of the economy hitting a new high ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"with Trump also above water on another important metric .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"On the heels of a better-than-expected quarter of GDP growth","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"( the US economy has grown at an average clip of better than three percent","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"since the GOP tax reform law was implemented ) ,","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"even a Trump-skeptical to -hostile electorate can recognize prosperity","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"when they see it .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"And the man at the top is getting credit :","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"CNN poll :","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Trump +15 on the economy , +4 on keeping promises .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"https : //t.co/1zW0e47qs","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"1 - Guy Benson","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"( @ guypbenson )","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"May 2 , 2019","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"President Trump ' s approval rating on the economy has hit a new high ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"according to a CNN poll","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"released on Thursday .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"A majority of respondents","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"- 56 percent -","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"they approve of Trump ' s handling of the economy ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"compared with 41 percent","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"who disapproved .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"The president 's previous high mark on the economy in the CNN poll came in March 2017 ,","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"when 55 percent approved of his work .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"I also find this nugget interesting :","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"`` Fifty percent of those","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"polled in the new survey said","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"he has done a good job","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"at keeping the promises","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"the made on the campaign trail .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Forty-six percent said","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"he had done a poor job","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"and 4 percent had no opinion . ''","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"This has to be welcome news to the re-elect team ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"considering Trump 's repeated use of the slogan , `` promises made ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"promises kept . ''","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"A majority of voters apparently agree .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"As for the downsides , the president is upside-down on healthcare","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"( 38 percent approval )","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"and immigration","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"( 42 percent approval )","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"-- and his overall job approval rating ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"despite hitting its best mark in this polling series in a year ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"is still only 43 percent .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Fifty-two percent disapprove .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"As I 've said before ,","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"Trump 's re-election will depend on the economy 's continued thriving , and his ability","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"to win over a significant chunk of voters","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"who approve of him on that issue ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"in spite of their qualms about his leadership on the whole .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"It could certainly help his cause","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"that leading Democratic presidential hopefuls continue to call for large tax increases on the middle class ,","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"having swallowed their own dishonest talking points about the Trump-signed tax cuts .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"As a refresher , 80 percent of all Americans received a tax cut in 2018","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"thanks to the new law ,","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"including roughly 91 percent of middle class filers .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Repealing that law ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"as Democrats are demanding ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"would jack up taxes on the lopsided majority of the electorate .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"Joe Biden got in on the act ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"falsely claiming","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that tax reform merely benefited the rich and corporations ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"earning himself Four Pinocchios from the Washington Post 's fact checker :","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"WaPo Fact checker :","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"Biden ' s false claim","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"that no one but the rich got Trump ' s tax cuts","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"https : //t.co/AqSGJLpklt","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"- Jake Tapper","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"( @ jaketapper )","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"May 1 , 2019","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"\" There ' s a $ 2 trillion tax cut last year .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Did you feel it ?","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Did you get anything from it ?","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Of course not .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Of course not .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"All of it went to folks at the top and corporations . \"","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"`` That 's simply wrong , ''","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"the Post concludes .","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"Indeed it is ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"and","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"by agitating for repeal ,","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"Democrats run the political risk","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"of being accurately painted as middle class tax-raisers .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"That would be the literal consequence of their preferred policy outcome .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Finally ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"since we 're on the subject of Trump approval ,","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"I 'll leave you with a progress report on perhaps his most important presidential legacy to date :","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"The Senate just confirmed President Trump ' s 100th judge .","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"https : //t.co/LQn2MQYSAK","depth":4},{"id":93,"text":"- Garrett Ventry","depth":5},{"id":94,"text":"( @ GarrettVentry )","depth":5},{"id":95,"text":"May 2 , 2019","depth":4},{"id":96,"text":"Here 's Mitch McConnell talking up that progress ,","depth":3},{"id":97,"text":"some of which he attributes to the `` modest step ''","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"we analyzed last month :","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":197,"left":186,"right":196,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":186,"left":147,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":115,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":112,"right":114,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":108,"right":111,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":108,"left":100,"right":107,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":107,"left":102,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":106,"left":104,"right":105,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":5,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":10,"right":110,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":109,"right":13,"relation":"explanation","nuclea